Gareth Southgate has reaffirmed his commitment to the FA by signing a 12-month contract extension.

The England Under 21 head coach, who has guided his squad to this summer European Championships, had 18 months remaining on his current deal.

Those terms would have expired in the middle of qualification for Euro 2017 and the FA were keen to extend his deal beyond that date to incorporate the tournament in its entirety.

