Southgate instructs his Under 21 players during a training session at St George's Park in October

Southgate took over from Stuart Pearce in August 2013 and has overseen a dramatic improvement, with the Under 21s winning 12 of the 14 matches he has been in charge for, suffering only one defeat in a friendly to France.

They will warm-up for Euro 2015 with friendlies in March against Czech Republic and Germany at the Riverside in Middleborough.

Southgate said: 'I am enjoying my work at The FA and with St. George’s Park coming to life with innovation and development across our football disciplines I believe we now have some solid foundations in place.

'England DNA is evolving but anyone who has seen our development teams play – including the Under 21s – will know that many of the principles can already been seen in the way we go about our work.

Alongside England manager Roy Hodgson (right), Southgate addresses the media at Wembley in 2013

